  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Disappointing &lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Karl&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was admitted to A&amp;amp;E via ambulance. The 45 minute wait for the ambulance was bad enough but on arrival to the hospital was faced with a further 2 hour + delay to be admitted. That is not my complaint. It is the miss management of the ambulance crew, who can I say were fantastic throughout. I was shocked to find that they had to wait with me until being handed over to the hospital. I was lucky as there was only one person in front of me but was informed by the ambulance crew sometimes when A&amp;amp;E is really busy this could run to several hours. This is appalling to think someone may require life threatening treatment and miss out due to all crews waiting to hand over their patients to hospital staff. Surely there has to be a better way to manage incoming patients in order to release the valuable ambulance crews back to doing what they do best.   &lt;/CommentText&gt;
